page.title: 12Helen's day in Wishford.
page.content: I wake up at about 6.45am I fetch my dog to bed or I read until I am told to get up at 7.30am.I have my breakfast,wash and dress for school. Then I feed my rabbit and walk my dog. At 8.45am I leave for school in mum's car.At school I enjoy writing and like the Domesday Project.At 3.15pm my sister and I are picked up by mum. At home I change and play with my sister on the bike or I take the dog for a walk.Sometimes I look at my horse things or my stamp collection with my dad,or I help my dad in the garden. At 5.30pm I go in for my tea.I watch television for an hour then I have a bath and go to bed at 7.30pm and read until 8.00pm.
